The paper deals with covert communications in wireless networks, which involves information theory (IT) and networking (NI) concepts. It also considers the impact of interference and detection, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (CR). The use of multi-antenna systems and optimization techniques suggests a focus on multimedia (MM) and systems and control (SY) sub-categories as well.
